2025-09-29 16:08:04,559 - INFO - LLM Optimization Results:
2025-09-29 16:08:04,559 - INFO - Strategy Summary: Key insights indicate that lower aspirate and dispense speeds paired with minimal wait times reduce cycle time, though potentially at the cost of increased deviation and variability. Conversely, higher aspirate and dispense speeds with longer wait times improve accuracy. A balanced approach can yield satisfactory performance across all metrics. Experiment 0 and 1 highlight the trade-offs between speed and accuracy, while Experiment 2 suggests a middle ground strategy.
2025-09-29 16:08:04,559 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 1:
2025-09-29 16:08:04,559 - INFO -   Confidence Level: medium
2025-09-29 16:08:04,559 - INFO -   Reasoning: This SPEED-FOCUSED approach adopts the lowest possible aspirate and dispense speeds to achieve faster cycles, with low wait times to minimize overall time. Although this may increase deviation and variability, it offers a potential for significantly reduced time based on the observation that Experiment 0 had a lower time of 43.04 seconds with moderate speeds and low wait times.
2025-09-29 16:08:04,559 - INFO -   Expected Improvement: Significant reduction in overall cycle time, potentially less than 40 seconds.
2025-09-29 16:08:04,569 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 2:
2025-09-29 16:08:04,569 - INFO -   Confidence Level: high
